GREGORY BULL, AP None Josh, a Newfoundland, runs with his tongue out next to handler Michelle Ostermiller while winning Best in Show at the Westminster Dog Show in 2004. GREGORY BULL, AP None C.J., a German shorthaired pointer, is shown in the ring during the sporting group competition at the 140th Westminster Kennel Club Dog Show Feb. 16, 2016, at Madison Square Garden in New York. C.J. won Best in Show after taking the top spot in the Sporting group. Mary Altaffer, AP None C.J., a German Short Haired Pointer, was a crowd pleaser. He won Best in Show at the 140th annual Westminster Kennel Club dog show at Madison Square Garden. Stephanie Keith, Getty Images None It's rare that a champion can sit in his or her trophy. But Malachy, a Pekingese, did it after being named best in show at the 136th annual Westminster Kennel Club Dog Show in New York on Feb. 14, 2012. Seth Wenig, AP None Sadie, a Scottish terrier, was Best in Show after winning the terrier group at the Westminster Kennel Club Dog Show at Madison Square Garden in 2010. Henny Ray Abrams, AP None In 2009, Stump the Sussex Spaniel won Best in Show. Here he stands with his trophy during the 133rd Westminster Kennel Club Dog Show at Madison Square Garden in New York. TIMOTHY A. CLARY, AFP/Getty Images None In 2013, an Affenpinscher named Banana Joe V. Tani Kazari took Best in Show. Here the dog is shown with handler Ernesto Lara during Toy Group judging. Eileen Blass, USA TODAY Sports None An Affenpinscher named Gch Banana Joe V Tani Kazari won Best In Show in 2013. Eileen Blass, USA TODAY Sports None In 1998, Champ Fairewood Frolic, a Norwich Terrier won the silver bowl after being named Best in Show at the Westminster Kennel Club Dog Show. RON FREHM, Associated Press None In 2001, a Bichon Frise named Special Times Just Right claimed Best in Show at the 125th Westminster Kennel Club Dog Show.
